  "title": "Planning Engineer (Construction, MS Project, Primavera P6)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Create, update, and manage project timelines to ensure efficient workflow and execution.</li>\n  <li>Monitor project schedules, track progress, and provide regular updates while identifying any deviations.</li>\n  <li>Analyse scheduling data, assess budget forecasts, and oversee cost estimations to maintain financial accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with engineering, procurement, and project teams to align work scope and prepare detailed reports for management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in any relevant discipline.</li>\n  <li>At least 4 years of project planning experience in <strong>Construction industry.</strong></li>\n  <li>Proficiency in <strong>Microsoft Project</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
